23/06/2005
LJUBLJANA, Slovenia-- Slovenian President Janez Drnovsek said in a media interview this week that bilateral ties with Croatia are improving. 
He added, however, that the main problem between the two countries -- the dispute over the interstate border -- must be resolved. 
Speaking on Slovenian television, Drnovsek described a recent meeting between the Croatian and Slovenian governments in Brijuni as a positive development
In other news, A new bridge over the Sava River, connecting Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Croatia, was formally inaugurated on Wednesday (22 June). 
Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader, BiH Deputy Prime Minister Barisa Colak and European Commission (EC) delegation chief Michael Humphreys attended the ceremony in Jasenovac. 
The new bridge was built where a previous one had been destroyed during the conflicts of the 1990s. 
The EC and the Croatian government co-financed the project. 
(Nezavisne novine, Vecernji list - 23/06/05; HINA, HRT - 22/06/05)
